Setup

# Load packages
library(magrittr)
library(tidyverse)  # load last to avoid masking by others
library(treemapify)


# Import data
trials <- read_csv("../../data/tidy_data/trials.csv")
gbd <- read_csv(
  "../../data/tidy_data/gbd.csv", col_types = cols(ID = col_character())
)

Create dataset.

# Only maintain up to level_four
treemaps <- 
  trials %>% 
  filter(is_eligible, is_condition_defined_in_gbd) %>%
  select(nct_id, gbd_condition_ids, status_june23_sc, n_sample) %>% 
  separate_rows(gbd_condition_ids, sep = "; ") %>% 
  right_join(gbd, by = c("gbd_condition_ids" = "ID")) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(level_four) & is.na(level_five))

# Remaining trials
sprintf("Number of remaining trials = %s", nrow(treemaps))
[1] "Number of remaining trials = 288"
# Create dataset
treemaps %<>%
  group_by(level_two, level_three, level_four, relative_both_dalys) %>% 
  summarise(
    sample_size = sum(n_sample),
    n_complete_enroll = sum(str_detect(status_june23_sc, "C|E|R"), na.rm = T),
    p_complete_enroll = mean(str_detect(status_june23_sc, "C|E|R"), na.rm = T)
  ) %>% 
  mutate(complete_enroll = case_when(
    is.na(p_complete_enroll) | is.nan(p_complete_enroll)  ~ NA_character_,
    p_complete_enroll > 0.5 ~ ">50%",
    p_complete_enroll < 0.25 ~ "0-25%",
    T ~ "25-50%"
  )) %>%
  mutate(complete_enroll = factor(complete_enroll)) %>% 
  ungroup()

Plot level_four

Using treemapify - same color across level_two, no complete_enroll.

# Create palette
colfunc <- colorRampPalette(c("red", "yellow", "green"))

# Plot
treemaps %>%
  mutate_at(vars(sample_size), na_if, 0) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(
    area = relative_both_dalys, 
    fill = sample_size,
    label = level_four,
    subgroup = level_two,
    subgroup2 = level_three
  ), color = "white") +
  geom_treemap(color = "white", size = 1) +
  geom_treemap_text(
    colour = "grey20", 
    place = "centre", 
    grow = T, 
    reflow = T, 
    min.size = 1,
    padding.x = unit(2, units = "mm"),
    padding.y = unit(2, units = "mm"),
  ) +
  geom_treemap_subgroup_border(color = "white", size = 5) +
  geom_treemap_subgroup2_border(color = "white", size = 2) +
  labs(fill = "Total sample") +
  theme(legend.title = element_text(vjust = 2)) +
  scale_fill_gradient(
    low = "#F2DF91",
    high = "#CE0A04",
    na.value = "grey90",
    name = "Total sample",
    labels = scales::comma
  )

Plot level_three

Create data.

treemaps <- 
  trials %>% 
  filter(is_eligible, is_condition_defined_in_gbd) %>%
  select(nct_id, gbd_condition_ids, status_june23_sc, n_sample) %>% 
  separate_rows(gbd_condition_ids, sep = "; ") %>% 
  right_join(gbd, by = c("gbd_condition_ids" = "ID")) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(level_three) & is.na(level_four)) %>% 
  group_by(level_two, level_three, relative_both_dalys) %>% 
  summarise(
    sample_size = sum(n_sample),
    n_complete_enroll = sum(str_detect(status_june23_sc, "C|E|R"), na.rm = T),
    p_complete_enroll = mean(str_detect(status_june23_sc, "C|E|R"), na.rm = T)
  ) %>% 
  mutate(complete_enroll = case_when(
    is.na(p_complete_enroll) | is.nan(p_complete_enroll)  ~ NA_character_,
    p_complete_enroll > 0.5 ~ ">50%",
    p_complete_enroll < 0.25 ~ "0-25%",
    T ~ "25-50%"
  )) %>%
  mutate(complete_enroll = factor(complete_enroll)) %>% 
  ungroup()

Plot.

# Plot
treemaps %>%
  mutate_at(vars(sample_size), na_if, 0) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(
    area = relative_both_dalys, 
    fill = sample_size,
    label = level_three,
    subgroup = level_two,
  ), color = "white") +
  geom_treemap(color = "white", size = 1, alpha = 0.85) +
  geom_treemap_text(
    aes(color = complete_enroll),
    place = "centre", 
    grow = T, 
    reflow = T, 
    min.size = 1,
    padding.x = unit(2, units = "mm"),
    padding.y = unit(2, units = "mm"),
    show.legend = T
  ) +
  geom_treemap_subgroup_border(color = "white", size = 5) +
  theme(
    legend.title = element_text(vjust = 2)
  ) +
  scale_color_manual(
    values = c("#5E4FA2", "#66C2A5"),
    guide = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size = 3)),
    name = "Complete or recruiting",
    na.value = "grey70"
  ) +
  scale_fill_gradient(
    low = "#F2DF91",
    high = "#CE0A04",
    na.value = "grey90",
    name = "Total sample",
    labels = scales::comma
  )

Maps

Participants

Create data.

# Get map
heat_map <- 
  trials %>% 
  select(nct_id, region = location_participants, n_sample) %>% 
  separate_rows(region, sep = "; ") %>% 
  group_by(region) %>% 
  summarise(sample_size = sum(n_sample, na.rm = T)) %>% 
  full_join(ggplot2::map_data('world'))

Identify non-matched regions.

heat_map %>% 
  filter(is.na(long)) %>% 
  select(region, sample_size) %>% 
  sable()
region sample_size
Eastern Europe 1025
1516388

Calculate country centroids. X = long, Y = lat.

# Extract world data
world <- rnaturalearth::ne_countries(scale = "medium", returnclass = "sf")

# Calculate centroids
world_centroids <- 
  world %>% 
  cbind(sf::st_coordinates(sf::st_centroid(world$geometry))) %>% 
  as_tibble %>% 
  select(centroid_long = X, centroid_lat = Y, region = name)

# Harmonize this map with the previous map
world_centroids %<>% 
  filter(region != "Hong Kong") %>% 
  mutate_at(vars(region), str_replace, "United Kingdom", "UK") %>%
  mutate_at(vars(region), str_replace, "United States", "USA") %>%
  mutate_at(vars(region), str_replace, "^Korea$", "South Korea") %>%
  mutate_at(vars(region), str_replace, "^Czech.*", "Czech Republic") %>%
  mutate_at(vars(region), str_replace, "^Congo$", "Democratic Republic of the Congo") %>%
  mutate_at(vars(region), str_replace, "Lao PDR", "Laos") %>%
  mutate_at(vars(region), str_replace, "Dem.*Korea", "North Korea")

# Retain centroids of countries with data
world_centroids %<>% 
  left_join(heat_map) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(sample_size)) %>% 
  distinct(centroid_long, centroid_lat, region)
country_centroids <- 
  read_csv("../../data/external_data/countries.csv") %>% 
  rename(region = name) %>% 
  filter(region != "Hong Kong") %>% 
  mutate_at(vars(region), str_replace, "United Kingdom", "UK") %>%
  mutate_at(vars(region), str_replace, "United States", "USA") %>%
  mutate_at(vars(region), str_replace, "^Korea$", "South Korea") %>%
  mutate_at(vars(region), str_replace, "^Congo \\[DRC\\]$", "Democratic Republic of the Congo") %>%
  mutate_at(vars(region), str_replace, "^Macedonia.*", "Macedonia") %>% 
  left_join(heat_map) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(sample_size)) %>% 
  distinct(longitude, latitude, region)

Tables

Investigators vs. Participants

Combinations of country investigators and participants with at least 5 studies.

# Create table
investigators_vs_participants <- 
  trials %>% 
  select(nct_id, starts_with("location"), n_sample) %>% 
  separate_rows(location_investigators, sep = "; ") %>% 
  separate_rows(location_participants, sep = "; ") %>%
  group_by(location_investigators, location_participants) %>% 
  summarise(studies_n = n(), size_n = sum(n_sample)) %>%
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(studies_prop = scales::percent(studies_n / sum(studies_n), 0.1)) %>% 
  mutate(size_prop = scales::percent(size_n / sum(size_n, na.rm = T), 0.1)) %>%
  filter(studies_n >= 5) %>% 
  select(starts_with("loc"), starts_with("studies"), starts_with("size")) %>% 
  arrange(desc(studies_n)) %>%
  mutate_if(is.numeric, scales::comma, accuracy = 1) %>% 
  mutate_all(replace_na, "(Missing)")

# Save
write_csv(
  investigators_vs_participants,
  "../../output/table_output/figures_investigators-vs-participants.csv"
)
